{"id":"project-LICHEN-t0oz","title":"router.c: fwd_stats increments are not atomic, causing race on stats","description":"File: lichen/subsys/lichen/routing/router.c
Lines: 873-876, 898-899, 988-989

In the forwarding buffer code, statistics are incremented without synchronization:

    router->fwd_stats.packets_dropped_full++;
    router->fwd_stats.nacks_sent++;
    ...
    router->fwd_stats.packets_queued++;
    ...
    router->fwd_stats.packets_dropped_deadline++;

If multiple threads call these functions concurrently (possible in a multi-core Zephyr system), the increments are not atomic, leading to lost increments or torn reads.

For statistics used for monitoring/debugging, this may be acceptable. But if the stats are used for flow control decisions, inaccurate counts could cause incorrect behavior.

Consider using atomic increments: k_atomic_inc() or __atomic_add_fetch().","status":"open","priority":3,"issue_type":"bug","owner":"me@mark.atwood.name","created_at":"2026-07-12T06:51:33.690572Z","created_by":"Mark Atwood","updated_at":"2026-07-12T06:51:33.690602Z"}
